The paper discusses clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with fairness in clustering, which is a topic of growing interest in the field, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely categories as well. The use of approximation algorithms and bicriteria analysis suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible categories.
